The paper discusses the PDDL language, which is commonly used in the field of automated planning and scheduling (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on the addition of durative actions and objective functions to PDDL2.1, which are features related to planning and optimization (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the semantics of these features, which is a topic in logic and reasoning (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions the implementation of PDDL in planning algorithms, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and robotics (cs.RO).
